Dorsal colouration pale (
Fig. 37a–d
): pronotum yellow with a thin brown band along anterior and posterior margins, with two poorly defined darker areas on disc. Elytra yellow with a brown pattern composed by longitudinal vittae, more or less confluent and broken, especially in subapical half, plus an external one reduced to a elongate macula. Sutural line very thin, black.
